abstract: With Israel’s prime minister under indictment, Gideon Saar is challenging him for the Likud party leadership. His chances may be slim, but he has cracked Likud’s united front.
snippet: With Israel’s prime minister under indictment, Gideon Saar is challenging him for the Likud party leadership. His chances may be slim, but he has cracked Likud’s united front.
lead_paragraph: OR YEHUDA, Israel — With Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel politically weakened and steeped in legal troubles, a rival from within his conservative Likud party has emerged to challenge his grip on the party leadership.

abstract: Canadian Adam Hadwin and South African Erik van Rooyen have snuck into the field for next year's Masters after finishing the year barely inside the top 50 in the world rankings.
snippet: Canadian Adam Hadwin and South African Erik van Rooyen have snuck into the field for next year's Masters after finishing the year barely inside the top 50 in the world rankings.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Canadian Adam Hadwin and South African Erik van Rooyen have snuck into the field for next year's Masters after finishing the year barely inside the top 50 in the world rankings.
headline_main: Golf: Hadwin, Van Rooyen Seeing Green After Sneaking Into Masters
headline_print_headline: Golf: Hadwin, Van Rooyen Seeing Green After Sneaking Into Masters

abstract: Chris Dailey remained perfect filling in for Geno Auriemma as head coach as No. 2 UConn stated its case to move up to the top of the poll.

lead_paragraph: UNCASVILLE, Conn. — Chris Dailey remained perfect filling in for Geno Auriemma as head coach as No. 2 UConn stated its case to move up to the top of the poll.

abstract: Timothy Polin winds us up with a Monday puzzle.
snippet: Timothy Polin winds us up with a Monday puzzle.
lead_paragraph: MONDAY PUZZLE — We’re in the throes of the holiday season, which I hope you’re all enjoying. It is a good time of the year for themes; I figure that constructors come up with festive seasonal ideas all year round that have to be jiggled in a pocket for months, sometimes, until they’re relevant.
